Violence erupted in the wee hours of Thursday in Mamelodi after a transformer was damaged and led to a blackout.According to formal housing residents the transformer was damaged because the informal settlement dwellers had illegally connected electricity directly from the transformer.This disagreement led to two groups clashing, which resulted in several houses and shacks been petrol bombed.Police spokesperson in the area Johannes Maheso said the police were monitoring the situation, adding that situation was under control. Public order policing officers are on the scene. They are monitoring the situation, Maheso said.No arrest have been made.-TNA Reporter